agreed.<br>
<br>
i began my paladin in early 2000. at the time there were not many weapons for a paladin that were much better. maybe on par, but not a lot that made sf trivial <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> to paladins</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as a weapon. soulfire at that time was a milestone in a paladin's career. it was the climax to a long quest which, if you try it in your 30's or low 40's does make it difficult, even now.<br>
<br>
after several mistarts, and a long hiatus, then active questing, camping, etc... i finally got soulfire last weekend. i was very pleased to do so. it was an accomplishment, a goal set out for and finally finished.<br>
<br>
sure there are better weapons. big deal. to the player that plays a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> paladin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for its sake or to the player that enjoys the quests and stories and lore of eq, this <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> weapon</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does make a difference.<br>
<br>
guess it depends on your gameplay perspective. it's not always about the loot or the best gear.<br>
